    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-28T13:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1415: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-28T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 28, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2331. Embassy, Vichy, requested repeat to you its 413, August 23, noon, and 430,
                    August 26, 1 p.m.<note n="57" xml:id="d216fn57">Neither printed.</note> Upon
                    receipt please request German Foreign Office urgently to consider the situation
                    of Americans in France desiring to return to United States, who are being
                    prevented from doing so by delay in obtaining exit visas from German authorities
                    and restrictions on exportation of currency. With respect to latter
                    restrictions, as it appears to be impossible for Americans in France to purchase
                    through transportation there to United States, they should at least be allowed
                    to depart with sufficient dollars or other currency to enable them to proceed
                    through Spain and Portugal and purchase transportation to New York from
                    Lisbon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
